GeoWin demos demonstrating various CGAL data structures
and algorithms.
LEDA 4.0 or higher is required.

CGAL2dtree.C / CGAL3dtree.C   : demonstrations of kd-trees 
CGALafn.C                     : all furthest neighbours
CGALcircle.C                  : optimisation - minimal enclosing circle
CGALdemo.C                    : simple demo that lets you construct some scenes of geometric objects
CGALdtfl.C                    : delaunay triangulation data type demonstration
CGALhull.C                    : 2d convex hull algorithm
CGALhull3d.C                  : 3d convex hull algorithm (use Show 3d output in the Window menu to view the
                                three dimensional output)
CGALmaxpoly.C                 : maximum area inscribed k-gon demo
CGALmin_ellipse.C             : optimisation demo for minimal enclosing ellipse
CGALpolyinout.C               : polygon inside/outside test for points
CGALsegint.C                  : 2d segment intersection
CGALtriang.C                  : this one demonstrates triangulations and voronoi diagrams
CGALplmap.C                   : simple planar map demo incl. ray shooting
CGALdt3d.C                    : 3d Delaunay triangulations
D2_demo.C                     : triangulations, Delaunay triangulations, Voronoi diagram,
                                crust, location on DT
CGALconstr_triang.C           : constrained triangulations
CGALmin_sphere                : smallest enclosing sphere demo (use Show 3d output in the Window menu to view the
                                three dimensional output)
CGALreg_triang.C              : regular triangulation


Note that some demos (like CGAL2dtree, CGALdtfl) use more then one input scene.
To activate the others, use the Scenes - activate menu.

